---
description: Check information_schema.columns before assuming a column exists on a table
globs: "**/*.sql"
alwaysApply: false
---

Before assuming a column exists on a table, verify it using the `postgres-readonly` MCP server:

```
tool: query
sql: SELECT column_name, data_type FROM information_schema.columns WHERE table_name = '<table_name>' ORDER BY ordinal_position
```

Prefer `schema://table/{table_name}` as a faster alternative when the MCP resource is available. Use `information_schema.columns` when you need data types, nullability, defaults, or cross-schema lookups.
